    "description": "<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">These range from a cheap pens in a plastic casing, and a unibody pen and nib combo, all the way to your premium ballpoints with interchangeable cartridges. Ballpoint pens use oil based ink, and have enough ink to scribe 30 spells before requiring the cartridge to be replaced or the entire pen body to be replaced.</span> <br style=\" font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; \"></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">These pens are a standard cheap bulk pack of pens used for everyday writing, note taking, and other miscellaneous writing. When they are empty, you throw them away. They come in packs of 30. Using a disposable pen increases the time it takes to scribe a spell by 2, rounded up to the nearest minute or Combat Point.</span> <br style=\" font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; \"></p>"
